a) Write a program to represent a bank account with the information given below:

- Minimum balance amount should be 500

- Deposited amount should be added to the available amount

PROGRAM

package bankaccount1;

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Bankaccount1 {

public String depositor_name;

public int acc_no;

public String acc_type;

public double bal_amt;

public void user_details()

{

Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);

System.out.println("Enter details for Depositor Name , Account No , Accounttype");

depositor_name = sc.nextLine();

acc_no=sc.nextInt();

acc_type=sc.next();

}

public double deposit()

{

Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);

System.out.println("Enter the amount to deposit");

double d=s.nextDouble();

bal_amt+=d;

return bal_amt;

}

public double withdraw()

{

Scanner s1=new Scanner(System.in);

System.out.println("Enter the amount to withdraw");

double w=s1.nextDouble();

bal_amt=w; return bal_amt; 
} 
public void display() { 
System.out.println("Depositor Name : "+depositor_name); 
System.out.println("Account No : "+acc_no); 
System.out.println("account type : "+acc_type); 
System.out.print("Balance amount : "+bal_amt); 
} 
public static void main(String[] args) { 
Bankaccount1 b =new Bankaccount1(); b.user_details(); 
while(true){ 
System.out.println("Enter your choice:\n1.Balance"+" \n2.Deposit\n3.Withdraw\n4.Exit"); 
Scanner s1=new Scanner(System.in); 
int c=s1.nextInt(); 
switch(c) { 
case 1: b.display(); 
break; 
case 2: 
b.deposit(); 
b.display(); 
break; 
case 3: 
b.withdraw(); 
b.display(); 
break; 
case 4: 
System.exit(0); 
break; 
default: System.out.println("Invalid choice"); 
break; 
} 
} 
} 
}

b) Design a class on the basis of the following information:

Monthly bill should be calculated according to the slabs mentioned below. It should also

display the total amount to be paid.

PROGRAM: 

import java.util.*; 
public class Elect_Bill 
{ 
public long cno; 
public String cname; 
public String cadd; 
public long nou; 
public double amt=0;
public Elect_Bill(long x,String y,String z,long n){ 
cno=x; 
cname=y; 
cadd=z;
nou=n; 
} 
public void display()
{ 
System.out.println("Customer No: "+cno); 
System.out.println("Customer Name: "+cname); 
System.out.println("Customer Address: "+cadd); 
System.out.println("Your Bill is Rupees: "+amt); } 
public double calculate(){ if(nou<=100){ amt+=500; } 
else if(nou>=100 && nou<=200)
{ 
long temp=nou-100; 
temp*=1; 
amt=500+temp;
} 
else if(nou>=200 && nou<=300)
{ 
long temp=nou-100; 
temp*=1.20; 
amt=500+temp; 
} 
else if(nou>300){ long temp=nou-100; 
temp*=1.50; 
amt=500+temp; 
} 
else 
{ 
System.out.println("Enter valid units"); 
} 
return amt; 
} 
public static void main(String[] s)
{ 
Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in); 
System.out.println("Enter CustomerNo, CustomerName, CustomerAdd, No. of Units: "); 
long x=sc.nextLong(); 
String y=sc.next();

String z=sc.next(); 
//sc.next(); 
long n=sc.nextLong(); 
Elect_Bill e=new Elect_Bill(x,y,z,n); 
e.calculate();
e.display(); 
} 
}
